WEBVTT

1
00:00:29.299 --> 00:00:30.383
Be not afraid.

2
00:00:31.426 --> 00:00:33.010
What's happening to me?

3
00:00:40.018 --> 00:00:41.852
- I can't see anything.
- Oh. God.

4
00:00:51.571 --> 00:00:53.824
Frances. Frances!

5
00:00:54.908 --> 00:00:55.909
Frances!

6
00:00:57.118 --> 00:00:58.578
Frances!

7
00:01:01.039 --> 00:01:02.707
- Frances?
- Help!

8
00:01:03.416 --> 00:01:04.750
Frances!

9
00:01:05.418 --> 00:01:06.585
Frances!

10
00:01:11.049 --> 00:01:12.050
Grab hold!

11
00:01:17.347 --> 00:01:19.474
Grab ahold.

12
00:01:25.313 --> 00:01:28.233
Hold on. I'm-I'm trying. Frances!

13
00:01:29.276 --> 00:01:30.526
Don't let go!

14
00:02:12.319 --> 00:02:14.070
You have to sound the siren. Tom.

15
00:02:15.322 --> 00:02:16.531
She's right.

16
00:02:17.073 --> 00:02:18.992
Those thunderheads ain't natural.

17
00:02:19.659 --> 00:02:22.704
Read the accounts of the Storm of 1783.

18
00:02:23.288 --> 00:02:27.125
Started with big. ugly
storm clouds just like that.

19
00:02:28.168 --> 00:02:31.296
Storm roared in like The Great Flood.

20
00:02:31.963 --> 00:02:35.257
Storm brought waterspouts and tornadoes.

21
00:02:35.258 --> 00:02:38.177
Men were ripped up into the black sky.

22
00:02:38.178 --> 00:02:41.139
Babies torn from their mothers' arms.

23
00:03:02.577 --> 00:03:03.578
How we looking?

24
00:03:04.287 --> 00:03:05.622
<i>You got your Doppler up?</i>

25
00:03:06.414 --> 00:03:07.415
Yeah.

26
00:03:09.751 --> 00:03:11.628
<i>It doesn't look great</i>.

27
00:03:13.129 --> 00:03:14.880
What's the mainland saying?

28
00:03:14.881 --> 00:03:17.884
<i>We lost contact with the mainland
20 minutes ago.</i>

29
00:03:20.178 --> 00:03:22.848
Okay. Well. then keep me updated.

30
00:03:30.021 --> 00:03:31.147
You have to sound the siren.

31
00:03:31.148 --> 00:03:33.150
You have to get everyone
into the shelters.

32
00:03:35.360 --> 00:03:37.112
Right now. it's just a storm.

33
00:03:39.573 --> 00:03:44.160
If I… If I sound the siren.
that's all they'll say when they get home.

34
00:03:44.161 --> 00:03:47.831
They went to Widow's Bay
and ended up in a fucking storm shelter.

35
00:03:48.415 --> 00:03:50.875
That doesn't happen
on Martha's Vineyard.

36
00:03:50.876 --> 00:03:52.294
At least they'll get back home.

37
00:03:53.795 --> 00:03:55.130
People have died. Tom.

38
00:04:33.585 --> 00:04:36.045
- Fuck.
- Oh. uh…

39
00:04:36.046 --> 00:04:37.172
Um…

40
00:04:37.923 --> 00:04:39.841
Shit. Shit. Shit.

41
00:04:41.426 --> 00:04:43.053
Fuck.

42
00:04:43.803 --> 00:04:46.680
Uh… Tom!

43
00:04:46.681 --> 00:04:48.433
Oh. my God.

44
00:04:50.393 --> 00:04:51.477
- You okay?
- No.

45
00:04:51.478 --> 00:04:53.688
My back. Can't move it.

46
00:04:54.523 --> 00:04:55.689
She's missing a finger.

47
00:04:55.690 --> 00:04:56.733
What?

48
00:04:57.776 --> 00:05:00.986
No. Patricia.
Patricia. Patricia.

49
00:05:00.987 --> 00:05:02.280
Patricia.

50
00:05:03.532 --> 00:05:05.991
- Oh. Kenny.
- Everybody stay back.

51
00:05:05.992 --> 00:05:08.744
- Oh. fuck.
- Tom. what happened?

52
00:05:08.745 --> 00:05:11.455
- Kenny.
- I said to stay back.

53
00:05:11.456 --> 00:05:14.000
- He might have broke something.
- No. Let him help me.

54
00:05:14.543 --> 00:05:16.877
- Maybe if we both grab a side. we can...
- Back off. Kenny.

55
00:05:16.878 --> 00:05:19.046
He might have spinal damage.
Can't move him.

56
00:05:19.047 --> 00:05:21.257
I'll do it myself. Here we go.

57
00:05:21.258 --> 00:05:23.467
- No. No.
- All right.

58
00:05:23.468 --> 00:05:25.678
You're pushing it down on me.
You're pushing it down on me.

59
00:05:25.679 --> 00:05:27.304
Don't speak. Tom.

60
00:05:27.305 --> 00:05:30.140
Your lungs might be collapsed.
All right. here we go. Ready?

61
00:05:30.141 --> 00:05:32.309
One. two. three.

62
00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:33.811
Ow! Oh. my sciatica.

63
00:05:33.812 --> 00:05:35.354
- Oh. Poor Rosemary.
- Shit.

64
00:05:35.355 --> 00:05:38.191
- Oh. no.
- What?

65
00:05:43.405 --> 00:05:44.948
Thanks. Kenny.

66
00:05:45.949 --> 00:05:47.450
Tom. her finger.

67
00:05:48.034 --> 00:05:50.536
Look. Tom. It's missing.

68
00:05:50.537 --> 00:05:51.912
What?

69
00:05:51.913 --> 00:05:53.081
Frances Warren.

70
00:05:53.623 --> 00:05:56.334
Her brother ran over her ring finger.
It's in Sarah Warren's journal.

71
00:05:59.379 --> 00:06:02.214
This woman in the painting.
Frances Fisher.

72
00:06:02.215 --> 00:06:04.384
mysteriously washed up on shore as a girl.

73
00:06:05.010 --> 00:06:07.094
This is Frances Warren.

74
00:06:07.095 --> 00:06:10.015
That's why Richard Warren's
bloodline didn't end with him.

75
00:06:10.724 --> 00:06:12.267
Because his daughter lived.

76
00:06:20.734 --> 00:06:21.735
Tom?

77
00:06:34.414 --> 00:06:36.374
Tom. are you listening to me?

78
00:06:46.343 --> 00:06:49.637
If that is Frances Warren.

79
00:06:49.638 --> 00:06:53.391
that's over 400 years
of ancestry to untangle.

80
00:06:54.226 --> 00:06:57.103
Rosemary probably
already has genealogy on Barnabus.

81
00:07:00.816 --> 00:07:03.026
And then what? We round them up?

82
00:07:25.674 --> 00:07:27.217
This is Loftis.

83
00:07:29.845 --> 00:07:30.887
Hit the siren.

84
00:07:53.285 --> 00:07:57.747
This ferry isn't coming.
and I wouldn't even get on it if it did.

85
00:07:58.957 --> 00:08:00.291
Can we please just go back home?

86
00:08:00.292 --> 00:08:03.837
No. listen. ferries operate
in storms all the time.

87
00:08:14.598 --> 00:08:15.599
Bechir.

88
00:08:16.725 --> 00:08:17.850
get me home.

89
00:08:20.103 --> 00:08:21.688
I just need to try one more thing.

90
00:08:22.355 --> 00:08:23.356
All right? Okay.

91
00:08:29.321 --> 00:08:30.404
Stop…

92
00:08:58.433 --> 00:09:00.685
So. what's the plan here?

93
00:09:01.186 --> 00:09:02.813
I'm getting the fuck off this island.

94
00:09:03.730 --> 00:09:05.148
I know how to operate a boat.

95
00:09:06.149 --> 00:09:07.776
Forty miles from the mainland.

96
00:09:08.443 --> 00:09:11.947
In a boat with a range of 15 miles tops
with a full tank.

97
00:09:12.948 --> 00:09:16.617
And even if you do somehow refuel

98
00:09:16.618 --> 00:09:20.622
while in the middle of this storm.
the waves'll capsize you.

99
00:09:21.748 --> 00:09:23.291
I can't have my child here.

100
00:09:25.961 --> 00:09:27.128
I understand that. but…

101
00:09:27.963 --> 00:09:30.297
That boat came here on a boat.

102
00:09:30.298 --> 00:09:32.592
Not gonna get you to the mainland in this.

103
00:10:00.036 --> 00:10:01.454
What have you told her?

104
00:10:05.375 --> 00:10:06.376
Nothing.

105
00:10:08.170 --> 00:10:09.588
I can't tell her anything.

106
00:10:14.885 --> 00:10:17.596
<i>Attention residents
and visitors to Widow's Bay.</i>

107
00:10:18.180 --> 00:10:22.099
<i>There is a mandatory storm advisory
by order of the mayor.</i>

108
00:10:22.100 --> 00:10:24.644
<i>Report to the shelter immediately.</i>

109
00:10:25.562 --> 00:10:28.315
<i>Attention residents
and visitors to Widow's Bay…</i>

110
00:11:12.776 --> 00:11:13.859
Sorry.

111
00:11:13.860 --> 00:11:16.028
All right everyone.
head towards my voice.

112
00:11:16.029 --> 00:11:18.782
Make this left. Make your way downstairs.

113
00:11:19.324 --> 00:11:22.034
Welcome to your first nor'easter. folks.

114
00:11:22.035 --> 00:11:26.331
After this. you're gonna be one of us.
A real New Englander.

115
00:11:26.957 --> 00:11:30.668
Heard it's. uh… Heard it's hitting
Martha's Vineyard pretty hard.

116
00:11:30.669 --> 00:11:33.839
Now you'll be refunded
by your accommodations for tonight.

117
00:11:34.714 --> 00:11:35.924
That money's already spent.

118
00:11:36.508 --> 00:11:38.051
Okay.

119
00:11:40.846 --> 00:11:41.847
Come here.

120
00:11:45.600 --> 00:11:48.769
I know. I know. I just… I had to make sure
PJ and those guys were all coming.

121
00:11:48.770 --> 00:11:51.689
Listen. I know we do this dance a lot.

122
00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:52.898
Today. please...

123
00:11:52.899 --> 00:11:54.733
- I'm not gonna go anywhere.
- Can you... Okay.

124
00:11:54.734 --> 00:11:56.026
- I promise.
- Okay. good.

125
00:11:56.027 --> 00:11:59.655
And hey. we can go
to a Sox game whenever. you know.

126
00:11:59.656 --> 00:12:01.825
I mean. they still have
half a season left. so…

127
00:12:05.078 --> 00:12:06.537
I love you. bud.

128
00:12:06.538 --> 00:12:07.997
All right. go downstairs.

129
00:12:07.998 --> 00:12:08.999
Okay.

130
00:12:11.126 --> 00:12:12.586
We have an issue.

131
00:12:13.503 --> 00:12:14.921
Generator's out.

132
00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:19.175
The emergency lights run on batteries.
They'll last a half hour.

133
00:12:19.176 --> 00:12:21.135
then the shelter goes pitch-black.

134
00:12:21.136 --> 00:12:22.678
Oh. my God.

135
00:12:22.679 --> 00:12:24.638
There's power surges
through the whole island.

136
00:12:24.639 --> 00:12:27.016
'Cause of the storm.
it's overloading the grid.

137
00:12:27.017 --> 00:12:29.226
Even the heavy-duty gear is getting fried.

138
00:12:29.227 --> 00:12:32.104
So-So what do we do?
We have to get power down there.

139
00:12:32.105 --> 00:12:33.772
Garrett might have a replacement.

140
00:12:33.773 --> 00:12:35.775
He's got the same one
up at the lighthouse.

141
00:12:37.694 --> 00:12:39.279
Garrett.

142
00:12:41.740 --> 00:12:44.116
Garrett. I'm looking right now.
I don't see you…

143
00:12:44.117 --> 00:12:45.951
Oh. oh. All right. listen. Listen to me.

144
00:12:45.952 --> 00:12:49.038
We need your starter
for the old generator.

145
00:12:49.039 --> 00:12:51.499
<i>I can't understand
a goddamn word you're saying.</i>

146
00:12:51.500 --> 00:12:52.833
Do...

147
00:12:52.834 --> 00:12:54.335
Does he not have a goddamn phone?

148
00:12:54.336 --> 00:12:56.213
No.

149
00:12:57.631 --> 00:12:58.714
Garrett.

150
00:12:58.715 --> 00:13:01.634
<i>How the hell am I
supposed to get you a goddamn starter?</i>

151
00:13:01.635 --> 00:13:04.053
Garrett. Garrett. I can't hear…

152
00:13:04.054 --> 00:13:06.889
We need your starter.

153
00:13:06.890 --> 00:13:08.599
This is an emergency.

154
00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:11.101
- I'm going up there.
- Tom. you shouldn't go out there.

155
00:13:11.102 --> 00:13:12.394
It's not safe.

156
00:13:36.586 --> 00:13:37.921
Let's get you warm.

157
00:13:38.421 --> 00:13:40.297
Let me help you.

158
00:13:40.298 --> 00:13:41.341
Okay.

159
00:13:42.843 --> 00:13:44.051
What's wrong. hon?

160
00:13:44.052 --> 00:13:46.596
Uh. maybe it's just Braxton Hicks.

161
00:13:48.390 --> 00:13:49.849
Dr. Morgan's downstairs.

162
00:13:49.850 --> 00:13:51.393
- Let's get you comfortable.
- Okay.

163
00:14:40.442 --> 00:14:42.651
You need to learn to knock. cowboy.

164
00:14:42.652 --> 00:14:44.946
This is a castle doctrine town.

165
00:14:45.447 --> 00:14:48.532
Funny to think the whole island survived

166
00:14:48.533 --> 00:14:51.369
on whale blubber
well into my father's day.

167
00:14:52.037 --> 00:14:54.247
The whaler. the captain. they…

168
00:14:54.956 --> 00:14:57.542
they owned this place. my daddy would say.

169
00:14:58.210 --> 00:15:00.045
What's this about. Wyck?

170
00:15:16.812 --> 00:15:18.813
I need you to do something for me.

171
00:16:31.219 --> 00:16:32.304
Garrett!

172
00:16:36.641 --> 00:16:37.726
Garrett!

173
00:16:40.061 --> 00:16:41.104
Fuck!

174
00:16:47.194 --> 00:16:49.362
No. No!

175
00:16:51.740 --> 00:16:52.741
Shit.

176
00:17:03.335 --> 00:17:04.336
Garrett?

177
00:17:06.796 --> 00:17:09.423
Goddamn it. Garrett.
I came here for the starter.

178
00:17:12.510 --> 00:17:14.512
Oh! Oh. thank God!

179
00:17:14.513 --> 00:17:16.430
- <i>I'll bring it back.</i>
- What? No. no. no!

180
00:17:16.431 --> 00:17:18.431
No. stay there. stay there!
I'm coming to you!

181
00:17:18.432 --> 00:17:21.142
I'm coming back!
I'm coming back!

182
00:17:21.143 --> 00:17:22.729
Dale. stop him!

183
00:17:45.919 --> 00:17:47.044
Fuck. No!

184
00:17:47.045 --> 00:17:50.006
No. no! Garrett!

185
00:17:50.507 --> 00:17:52.174
No.

186
00:17:52.175 --> 00:17:53.968
Garrett. go!

187
00:17:53.969 --> 00:17:56.638
Go. go. go. go. go!

188
00:17:57.180 --> 00:17:59.557
Get inside! Get inside!

189
00:17:59.558 --> 00:18:01.934
Hey. Wyck! Hey. hey. Wyck!

190
00:18:01.935 --> 00:18:03.937
- Shaman?
- Wyck!

191
00:18:04.437 --> 00:18:05.813
Come inside!

192
00:18:05.814 --> 00:18:07.982
- Help me out!
- No. no. no! Come inside!

193
00:18:07.983 --> 00:18:10.109
No. no. come on!

194
00:18:10.110 --> 00:18:11.318
Help me. man!

195
00:18:11.319 --> 00:18:12.945
No. no! Leave it. leave it!

196
00:18:12.946 --> 00:18:15.614
- I need these!
- Come inside!

197
00:18:18.827 --> 00:18:20.745
Come inside! Come inside right now!

198
00:18:21.621 --> 00:18:23.164
Wyck!

199
00:19:00.285 --> 00:19:01.785
No one leaves this shelter.

200
00:19:01.786 --> 00:19:03.787
Do you understand? No matter what happens.

201
00:19:03.788 --> 00:19:06.040
Ruth's not here.

202
00:19:06.041 --> 00:19:07.374
She's home.

203
00:19:07.375 --> 00:19:08.459
Alone.

204
00:19:08.460 --> 00:19:11.504
Okay. all right.
I'll-I'll-I'll figure something out.

205
00:19:11.505 --> 00:19:13.422
We won't leave her out there.

206
00:19:20.972 --> 00:19:21.973
Loftis.

207
00:19:27.270 --> 00:19:29.189
There's something you both should see.

208
00:19:40.867 --> 00:19:42.077
What is this?

209
00:19:43.119 --> 00:19:44.830
I had her run a genealogy.

210
00:19:46.498 --> 00:19:49.333
You-You-You can't be serious.
Th-This-This is…

211
00:19:49.334 --> 00:19:51.377
- Wyck. we don't have time for that.
- I had to know.

212
00:19:51.378 --> 00:19:53.170
Know what. Wyck?

213
00:19:53.171 --> 00:19:58.260
Turned out Richard Warren
has one last living descendant.

214
00:20:01.221 --> 00:20:02.222
One?

215
00:20:02.973 --> 00:20:04.056
Who is it?

216
00:20:04.057 --> 00:20:06.809
No. Don't answer that.
It doesn't matter who it is.

217
00:20:06.810 --> 00:20:09.020
- We're not...
- Who is it?

218
00:20:09.729 --> 00:20:11.480
- Have a seat.
- Goddamn it. Rosemary!

219
00:20:11.481 --> 00:20:13.358
We don't have time for this.
Tell me who it is.

220
00:20:26.580 --> 00:20:28.790
Tom. you're not really
gonna listen to this.

221
00:20:43.054 --> 00:20:44.431
All right. Here we go.

222
00:20:46.600 --> 00:20:51.061
Warren and the first wife. Sybil.
lost their first two boys

223
00:20:51.062 --> 00:20:53.148
when they reached the island.

224
00:20:53.648 --> 00:20:57.943
As for the others.
didn't work out so well for them either.

225
00:20:57.944 --> 00:21:01.572
Nope. Tough break. Sorry. kid.

226
00:21:01.573 --> 00:21:03.574
Better luck next time.

227
00:21:03.575 --> 00:21:05.911
Okay. I want you to picture this.

228
00:21:06.578 --> 00:21:10.539
You're a little girl. and your finger
gets broken off by a wagon wheel.

229
00:21:10.540 --> 00:21:13.042
Next thing you know. your dad's dead.

230
00:21:13.043 --> 00:21:15.920
and your stepmom
is taking you on an adventure.

231
00:21:15.921 --> 00:21:17.714
Destination? Hell.

232
00:21:18.381 --> 00:21:19.508
Your name?

233
00:21:20.091 --> 00:21:23.094
Frances Warren.

234
00:21:23.845 --> 00:21:25.596
Now. your siblings are dead.

235
00:21:25.597 --> 00:21:27.848
but God's finger flicks you
on the back of the head.

236
00:21:27.849 --> 00:21:29.475
and you float back to shore.

237
00:21:29.476 --> 00:21:33.103
Lucky you. Barnabus Fisher finds you
on his way back from a whaling trip.

238
00:21:33.104 --> 00:21:35.356
takes pity on you. little girl.

239
00:21:35.357 --> 00:21:38.108
Feeds you. clothes you. raises you.

240
00:21:38.109 --> 00:21:39.528
Wealthy man.

241
00:21:40.529 --> 00:21:42.239
It must be nice.

242
00:21:46.117 --> 00:21:49.663
All right. Where was I?

243
00:21:50.622 --> 00:21:54.667
Fast forward a few years
and you're in the bloom of youth.

244
00:21:54.668 --> 00:21:56.961
No. I can't hear.

245
00:21:56.962 --> 00:21:58.880
I… I can't hear.

246
00:22:01.925 --> 00:22:05.262
Okay. You're 14 years old.

247
00:22:05.929 --> 00:22:08.056
Barnabus starts
to look at you differently.

248
00:22:08.765 --> 00:22:11.517
He sits you down
over a cup of whale fin soup

249
00:22:11.518 --> 00:22:14.353
and he tells you
things are gonna be different.

250
00:22:14.354 --> 00:22:18.399
He's ripping pages off the calendar.
X. X. X. He's counting down.

251
00:22:18.400 --> 00:22:21.235
Get you a white dress.
takes you to the pastor who says.

252
00:22:21.236 --> 00:22:23.195
"All right. I guess."
And now you're married.

253
00:22:23.196 --> 00:22:25.156
You suffer a few miserable years.

254
00:22:25.157 --> 00:22:29.244
Barnabus drops dead.
leaving you his whaling business

255
00:22:30.620 --> 00:22:31.997
and also a son.

256
00:22:32.664 --> 00:22:35.541
Jonathan is a healthy baby boy.

257
00:22:35.542 --> 00:22:38.962
and when he grows up.
he won't be shooting blanks.

258
00:22:39.880 --> 00:22:41.381
He is a stud.

259
00:22:42.215 --> 00:22:46.677
Now. here is where we reach
a few ends that are dead.

260
